{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ff49e1b9-f800-4667-ad71-16ed078372b7","content":"Neither — use **`dotnet watch`**.\n\n`dotnet watch` is the command that enables hot reload. It monitors your source files and automatically rebuilds/reruns when changes are detected:\n\n```bash\n# For running an app\ndotnet watch run\n\n# For running tests\ndotnet watch test\n```\n\n- **`dotnet run`** / **`dotnet test`** execute once and exit — no file watching or hot reload.\n- **`dotnet watch`** wraps those commands, adding the hot reload capability.\n\nThe environment variable you set (likely `DOTNET_WATCH_RESTART_ON_RUDE_EDIT`) only takes effect when running under `dotnet watch`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f5eee015-0fd1-4844-ae24-d55e90be4c48","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET hot reload - specifically whether they should use `dotnet test` or `dotnet run` to benefit from hot reload. Let me look at their project to understand the context better.","outputTokens":218,"requestId":"E3D5:2B8350:6F9DBB:800504:6A0529EE"},"id":"59f7b378-e981-4364-998d-bd52a445dcce","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:48:37.990Z","parentId":"ffa1d8b9-3ddb-4679-bac0-60978537faf8"}
